-- Peru’s New-Vehicle Sales Rise to Record in 2011, Andina Says
-- B y   A l e x   E m e r y
-- 2012-01-10T20:13:01Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-10/peru-s-new-vehicle-sales-rise-to-record-in-2011-andina-says.html
Peru ’s new-vehicle sales rose to a
record last year as economic  growth  spurred consumer demand,
state news agency  Andina  reported.  Sales increased 24 percent to 150,037 units in 2011 from
120,800 in 2010, Andina said, citing Peru’s car-dealers
association  Araper .  Toyota Motor Corp. (7203)  led 2011 sales with 24,507 units, while
 Hyundai Motor Co. (005380)  sold 20,366,  Kia Motors Corp. (000270)  sold 13,513 and
 Nissan Motor Co. (7201)  sold 13,140. Passenger cars accounted for 62
percent of sales, followed by vans with 24 percent, Andina said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alex Emery in Lima at 
